   <head>To POLLY LAURENCE, quitting the Pump. BATH, January 1756.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="1" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">SPITE of beauty, air, and grace,</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">With honour hast thou run thy race!</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">In  well thy part thou'st play'd â€”</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Now, sweet Polly, seek the</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="2" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="5" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">The prudent general, tho' beat,</l>
     <l n="6" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Reaps honour from</l>
     <l n="7" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">But nobler thou, thy thousands kill'd,</l>
     <l n="8" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">With  leav'st the field.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="3" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="9" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Let not retirement give the spleen,</l>
     <l n="10" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Thy sex's</l>
     <l n="11" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">But teach the vicious and the vain,</l>
     <l n="12" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Their pleasure's but refining pain.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="4" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="13" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Teach the gay by thy retreat,</l>
     <l n="14" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Eternal  is not wit;</l>
     <l n="15" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">And the formal fool advise,</l>
     <l n="16" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">cannot make her</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="5" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="17" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Take with thee to thy private state</l>
     <l n="18" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Th' applauses of the  and</l>
     <l n="19" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">The best reward below allow'd</l>
     <l n="20" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Of a conduct  and</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
